{
  "synopsis": "Eikou Naki Tensai-tachi: Kara no Monogatari is a documentary anime series produced by NHK, based on the manga 'Eikou Naki Tensai-tachi' (Geniuses Without Glory) written by Tomoyoshi Itou and illustrated by Shingo Morita, serialized in Weekly Young Jump. The anime focuses on the little-known stories of Japanese athletes who made significant yet unrecognized contributions to their respective sports. Each episode combines animation and real-life commentary from experts and sports legends. The first episode centers on Hironoshin Furuhashi, the renowned 'flying fish of Fujiyama,' and features commentary from Olympic swimmer Kousuke Kitajima and other notable figures, exploring Furuhashi's legacy and the development of competitive swimming in Japan.",
  "status": "completed",
  "episodes": 2,
  "characters": [
    {
      "name": "Hironoshin Furuhashi",
      "bio": "A legendary Japanese swimmer, known as the 'flying fish of Fujiyama,' who set multiple world records in freestyle swimming post-WWII and played a pivotal role in reviving Japanese competitive swimming on the world stage. He later served as president of the Japan Swimming Federation, contributing to the sport's development.",
